cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Energy Consumption and Per‑Packet Latency Measurements for Configurable Load‑Generator
  and L2 Forwarding Experiments
abstract: The dataset captures synchronized experiments in which a MoonGen load‑generator
  drives a libmoon network device under test with varying packet rates and sizes,
  while a separate layer‑2 forwarding workload runs on the same DUT. For each of six
  looped runs per configuration, per‑packet latency is recorded to CSV, filtered histograms
  are produced, and total energy consumption of the DUT is logged. The results include
  raw latency traces, aggregated plots, and energy logs, enabling quantitative analysis
  of performance–energy trade‑offs across multiple traffic configurations.
